    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Ewing</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department learns that Belgian Government has withdrawn prohibition against
                    importation of cattle from Holland, subject to inspection on arrival. You will
                    strongly urge similar withdrawal of prohibition against cattle from United
                    States, adducing the rigid inspection to which they are subjected from the
                    breeding grounds to the moment of shipment and the successful stamping out of
                    pleuro-pneumonia and other contagious diseases. No country so effectively
                    assures health of exported cattle as ours does, or has better ground to
                    remonstrate against exclusion from foreign ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
